We often perceive the physical world as being deeply influenced by a spiritual reality. In times of crisis—be it health challenges, economic hardship, or personal milestones—it is standard practice to combine scientific efforts with prayer and spiritual intervention. Many Nigerians hold the view that science and technology are tools provided by the Divine, but that placing absolute reliance on them while ignoring the spiritual dimension is a form of spiritual negligence. Because of this, there is a pervasive feeling that modernity, characterized by a rapid, often secular, scientific expansion, has caused a decline in the moral and spiritual anchoring that our society values. Therefore, many would agree that society has leaned too far into materialist/scientific explanations while neglecting the essential role of faith.

